  <!-- FAQ -->
  <h2 id="faq" class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4 mt-10">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="space-y-3 mb-8 not-prose">
    <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-gold/40 p-5 shadow-sm">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">Are generic disc stack centrifuge parts as good as OEM?</summary>
      <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">High-quality generic parts from reputable suppliers meet or exceed OEM material and dimensional specifications at roughly 50% less cost. However, low-cost generics from some manufacturers may not meet minimum specifications. Dolphin Centrifuge supplies both OEM and vetted aftermarket parts for Alfa Laval centrifuges.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-gold/40 p-5 shadow-sm">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">Which centrifuge brands have the best parts availability?</summary>
      <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Alfa Laval centrifuges have the widest parts availability worldwide, with both OEM and generic options. Westfalia (GEA) parts are more restricted and expensive. Smaller European brands (Flottweg, Veronesi, Seital) often require factory-sourced parts with long lead times.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-gold/40 p-5 shadow-sm">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">Does Dolphin Centrifuge supply OEM and generic centrifuge parts?</summary>
      <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Yes. Dolphin Centrifuge offers high-quality generic parts for Alfa Laval centrifuges as well as OEM parts for both Alfa Laval and Westfalia (GEA) centrifuges. All generic parts are sourced from reputable manufacturers who meet or beat OEM specifications.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-gold/40 p-5 shadow-sm">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">Why are Chinese disc centrifuge parts hard to source?</summary>
      <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Chinese disc centrifuges are typically clones of Alfa Laval or Westfalia designs with minor differences that make parts unique to each manufacturer. Spare parts are usually only available from the original Chinese manufacturer, making long-term maintenance difficult outside of China.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="bg-white rounded-xl border-l-4 border-gold/40 p-5 shadow-sm">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">How much does a typical disc centrifuge wear part cost?</summary>
      <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Wear parts like O-rings, gaskets, and seals are inexpensive — typically $5–$50 per piece. Major components such as bowl spindles or bull gears range from $350–$3,150 for generic parts vs $1,850–$3,550 for OEM. Buying quality generic parts from vetted suppliers can cut maintenance costs by 50% or more compared to OEM pricing.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
